			[1265] heading 'MathJax'
			[1267] heading 'Beautiful math in all browsers'
			[1269] paragraph ''
				[1270] link 'GitHub release version', url='https://img.shields.io/github/v/release/mathjax/MathJax-src.svg?sort=semver'
					[1271] image 'GitHub release version', url='https://img.shields.io/github/v/release/mathjax/MathJax-src.svg?sort=semver'
				StaticText ''
				[1272] link 'GitHub release version (v2)', url='https://img.shields.io/github/package-json/v/mathjax/MathJax/legacy-v2.svg?label=release-v2'

				[1279] link 'jsdelivr rank', url='https://flat.badgen.net/jsdelivr/rank/npm/mathjax?color=green'
					[1280] image 'jsdelivr rank', url='https://flat.badgen.net/jsdelivr/rank/npm/mathjax?color=green'

					[1282] image 'jsDelivr hits (npm)', url='https://img.shields.io/jsdelivr/npm/hm/mathjax'
				StaticText ''
				[1283] link 'npm monthly downloads (full)', url='https://img.shields.io/npm/dm/mathjax?label=npm'
					[1284] image 'npm monthly downloads (full)', url='https://img.shields.io/npm/dm/mathjax?label=npm'
				StaticText ''
				[1285] link 'npm total downloads', url='https://img.shields.io/npm/dt/mathjax.svg?style=flat&label=npm%20total'
					[1286] image 'npm total downloads', url='https://img.shields.io/npm/dt/mathjax.svg?style=flat&label=npm%20total'
			[1287] paragraph ''
				StaticText 'MathJax is an open-source JavaScript display engine for LaTeX, MathML, and AsciiMath notation that works in all modern browsers. It was designed with the goal of consolidating the recent advances in web technologies into a single, definitive, math-on-the-web platform supporting the major browsers and operating systems. It requires no setup on the part of the user (no plugins to download or software to install), so the page author can write web documents that include mathematics and be confident that users will be able to view it naturally and easily. Simply include MathJax and some mathematics in a web page, and MathJax does the rest.'
			[1288] paragraph ''
				StaticText 'Some of the main features of MathJax include:'
			[1289] list ''
				[1290] listitem ''
					ListMarker '•'
					[1291] paragraph ''
						StaticText 'High-quality display of LaTeX, MathML, and AsciiMath notation in HTML pages'
				[1292] listitem ''
					ListMarker '•'
					[1293] paragraph ''
						StaticText 'Supported in most browsers with no plug-ins, extra fonts, or special setup for the reader'
				[1294] listitem ''
					ListMarker '•'
					[1295] paragraph ''
						StaticText 'Easy for authors, flexible for publishers, extensible for developers'
				[1296] listitem ''
					ListMarker '•'
					[1297] paragraph ''
						StaticText 'Supports math accessibility, cut-and-paste interoperability, and other advanced functionality'
				[1298] listitem ''
					ListMarker '•'
					[1299] paragraph ''
						StaticText 'Powerful API for integration with other web applications'
			[1300] paragraph ''
				StaticText 'See'
				[1301] link 'http://www.mathjax.org/', url='http://www.mathjax.org/'
				StaticText 'for additional details about MathJax, and'
				[1302] link 'https://docs.mathjax.org', url='https://docs.mathjax.org/'
				StaticText 'for the MathJax documentation.'
			[1303] heading 'MathJax Components'
			[1305] paragraph ''
				StaticText 'MathJax version 3 uses files called'
				[1306] emphasis ''
					StaticText 'components'
				StaticText 'that contain the various MathJax modules that you can include in your web pages or access on a server through NodeJS. Some components combine all the pieces you need to run MathJax with one or more input formats and a particular output format, while other components are pieces that can be loaded on demand when needed, or by a configuration that specifies the pieces you want to combine in a custom way. For usage instructions, see the'
				[1307] link 'MathJax documentation', url='https://docs.mathjax.org/'
				StaticText '.'
			[1308] paragraph ''
				StaticText "Components provide a convenient packaging of MathJax's modules, but it is possible for you to form your own custom components, or to use MathJax's modules directly in a node application on a server. There are"
				[1309] link 'web examples', url='https://github.com/mathjax/MathJax-demos-web'
				StaticText 'showing how to use MathJax in web pages and how to build your own components, and'
				[1310] link 'node examples', url='https://github.com/mathjax/MathJax-demos-node'
				StaticText 'illustrating how to use components in node applications or call MathJax modules directly.'
			[1311] heading "What's in this Repository"
			[1313] paragraph ''
				StaticText 'This repository contains only the component files for MathJax, not the source code for MathJax (which are available in a separate'
				[1314] link 'MathJax source repository', url='https://github.com/mathjax/MathJax-src/'
				StaticText '). These component files are the ones served by the CDNs that offer MathJax to the web. In version 2, the files used on the web were also the source files for MathJax, but in version 3, the source files are no longer on the CDN, as they are not what are run in the browser.'
			[1315] paragraph ''
				StaticText 'The components are stored in the'
				[1316] code ''
					StaticText 'es5'
				StaticText 'directory, and are in ES5 format for the widest possible compatibility. In the future, we may make an'
				[1317] code ''
					StaticText 'es6'
				StaticText 'directory containing ES6 versions of the components.'
			[1318] heading 'Installation and Use'
			[1320] heading 'Using MathJax components from a CDN on the web'
			[1322] paragraph ''
				StaticText 'If you are loading MathJax from a CDN into a web page, there is no need to install anything. Simply use a'
				[1323] code ''
					StaticText 'script'
				StaticText 'tag that loads MathJax from the CDN. E.g.,'
			[1326] code ''
				StaticText '<script'
				StaticText 'id='
				StaticText '"MathJax-script"'
				StaticText ''
				StaticText 'async'
				StaticText ''
				StaticText 'src='
				StaticText '"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js"'
				StaticText '></script>'
			[1335] button ''
				[1336] image ''
